      "rationale": "NIH is an accepted surrogate for clinical hemolysis and is directly compared against clinical thresholds. The mapping from CFD shear stress to NIH uses the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power law model, which is known to have limitations at low-shear conditions relevant to VAD operation, partially limiting the relevance."
    },
    {
